All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ActiveActor
Abstract class representing an active actor in the game.
ActiveActorDestructible
Abstract class representing an active actor that is destructible.
ActorManager
Manages the actors in the game, including friendly units (such as the user's plane), enemy units, and projectiles.
Boss
Represents the Boss enemy in Level 2 of the game.
BossConfig
Configuration class for the Boss enemy in Level 2.
BossProjectile
Represents the projectile fired by the Boss in Level 2.
Challenge
The Challenge class represents a specific challenge level in the game.
ChallengeConfig
The ChallengeConfig class contains configuration constants for the Challenge level.
CollisionHandler
Handles the collision detection and response between different actors which are projectiles and planes in the game.
Destructible
Represents an entity that can be destroyed or take damage.
EnemyLevel1
Represents the enemy for Level 1
EnemyLevelThree
Represents an enemy in Level 3 of the game.
EnemyProjectile
Represents a projectile fired by the enemy in the game.
ExplosionImage
Represents an explosion visual effect in the game.
FighterPlane
Abstract class representing a fighter plane that is destructible and capable of firing projectiles.
GameController
The GameController class is responsible for managing the game flow, transitioning between levels, and handling game events such as starting a level, retrying a level, and showing error alerts.
GameOverImage
This class represents a "Game Over" image displayed in the game.
HeartDisplay
Represents a visual display of hearts in the game.
LevelOne
Represents Level 1 of the game.
LevelOneConfig
Configuration class for Level 1 of the game.
LevelParent
The abstract class representing a level in the game.
LevelThree
Represents the third level of the game.
LevelThreeConfig
Configuration class for Level Three.
LevelTwo
Represents Level 2 of the game, where the player faces off against a Boss.
LevelTwoConfig
Configuration class for Level 2.
LevelView
This class represents the visual aspects of a level in the game.
LevelViewLevelTwo
The LevelView for Level 2 of the game.
Main
Main class for launching the JavaFX application.
PauseScreen
The PauseScreen class provides functionality for managing the pause screen during the game.
Projectile
Abstract class representing a projectile that is destructible.
Scoreboard
The Scoreboard class manages the display and storage of the top 3 scores for the game.
ShieldImage
Represents the shield image that can be displayed around the Boss.
UIController
Class to control all UI features before the game
UIManager
UIManager handles the management and updating of the game's user interface elements such as the score, kill count, and scoreboard.
UserPlane
Represents the user-controlled plane in the game.
UserProjectile
Represents a projectile fired by the user plane in the game.
UserShield
This class represents the shield for the user's plane in Level Three.
WinImage
This class represents a "You Win" image displayed in the game.
